@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} is a BlueWave compatible Mail Door for Xenolink BBS Software.


 Why XenoBlue?

 There wasn't any good Blue Wave door for Xenolink.

 Why Blue Wave?

 The Blue Wave format was designed as a superior method of providing
 offline mail capabilities, particularly for networks based on the
 FidoNet standard (which means full support for FidoNet-style private
 mail, or NetMail).

 With the Blue Wave system you can read, write and configure offline
 using a program as @{"AmyBW" link "AmyBW" 0} or @{"QBlue" link "QBlue" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"

 - @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} is Xenoware (freely distributable for Xenolink sysops)
 - full configurable ansi menus and texts
 - compatible with the BlueWave 2.0 packet format
 - @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} has been tested for more than a year

Files included with @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}

 XenoBlue
 XenoBlue.bulletins
 XenoBlue.guide
 XenoBlue.guide.info
 XenoBlue.setup
 0 (dir)
   ConfigurationHelp
   ConfigurationMenu
   ConfigurationMenuExpert
   Intro
