   MainMenuExpert
   XenoBlue.TXT

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"


1) Create a directory called 'XenoBlue' in your 'Doors' directory.

2) Copy all the files to that directory.

3) Create an item for @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} in one of your BBS menus. @{"Example" link "MenuExample" 0}

4) Edit the @{"XenoBlue.setup" link "XBsetup" 0} file.

5) Tell your users to use a BW compatible reader as @{"AmyBW" link "AmyBW" 0} or @{"QBlue" link "QBlue" 0}

@endnode

@node "XBsetup" "XenoBlue.setup"

 Keyword         Value           Info
 --------------  --------------  --------------------------------
 SYSOP_NAME      <string/41>     Name used on the BBS name
 SYSTEM_NAME     <string/65>     Name of your BBS
 PACKET_ID       <string/8>      Base name of the mail packets
 DEFAULT_ADDRESS <fido address>  Default network address

 MAX_FILE_REQUEST<nr> <access>   Maximum file requests (MAX 10)

 FORCE_SECTION   <section range> Sysop forced section. (MAX 40)
 DEFAULT_SECTION <section range> Automatically preselected sections (MAX 40)

 HOLD_NETMAIL    <access>        Allow netmail on hold
 CRASH_NETMAIL   <access>        Allow crash netmail

 WORK_DIRECTORY  <directory>     Work directory
 LOCAL_DOWNLOAD  <directory>     Directory to copy mail packets to
 LOCAL_UPLOAD    <directory>     Directory with reply packets

 INITIAL_MSGS    <number>        Max messages per area for initial download

 ARCHIVER_NAME   <string/3>      Archiver name           (MAX 4)
 ARCHIVER_ID     <string/8>      Archiver signature      (MAX 4)
 MASH_COMMAND    <string/80>     Archiver mash command   (MAX 4)
 UNMASH_COMMAND  <string/80>     Archiver unmash command (MAX 4)

 UNLISTED_NODES  <none>          Allow netmail to unlisted systems.

 MAX_PACKET_SIZE <bytes>         Maximum (unmashed) mail packet size



 NOTES: <directory> MUST end with a slash or colon!! ( / or : )
        <access> can be level ranges and/or user names.
        use for packet_id only uppercase characters ("A" to "Z") and
        digits ("0" to "9") for full BlueWave compatibility.

 @{"Example" link "XBsetupExample" 0}

@endnode

@node "XBsetupExample" "Example"

 SYSOP_NAME         Richard de Vos
 SYSTEM_NAME        Foxhunt  BBS
 PACKET_ID          FOXHUNT
 DEFAULT_ADDRESS    2:286/414.0

 MAX_FILE_REQUEST    1   0-9
 MAX_FILE_REQUEST    4  10-60
 MAX_FILE_REQUEST   10  60-255,Leon_Makkink,John_Doe

 FORCE_SECTION      0,10,20
 DEFAULT_SECTION    1-5,100,200,350

 HOLD_NETMAIL       200-255,Leon_Makkink,John_Doe,Mister_X
 CRASH_NETMAIL      "Ron Lem" "Leon Makkink"

 WORK_DIRECTORY     RAM:T/
 LOCAL_UPLOAD       Up:
 LOCAL_DOWNLOAD     Down:

 INITIAL_MSGS       25

 ;----------------------;
 ; Archiver definitions ;
 ;----------------------;

 ARCHIVER_NAME      LHA
 ARCHIVER_ID        ??-lh?-
 MASH_COMMAND       LhA -m a @F @I#?
 UNMASH_COMMAND     LhA -m x @F

 ARCHIVER_NAME      ZIP
 ARCHIVER_ID        PK??
 MASH_COMMAND       Zip -k

 ARCHIVER_NAME      LZX
 ARCHIVER_ID        LZX?
 MASH_COMMAND       LZx -m1 -X0 a @F
 UNMASH_COMMAND     LZx -m1 -X0 x @F

 ARCHIVER_NAME      LH0
 ARCHIVER_ID        ??-lh0
 MASH_COMMAND       LhA -m -z a @F @I#?
 UNMASH_COMMAND     LhA -m x @F

 UNLISTED_NODES

 MAX_PACKET_SIZE    1000000

@endnode

@node "MenuExample" "Example"

 (this is for 2 nodes)

CMD = "X"
   {
      XenolinkDoor "^4096^2^Doors:XenoBlue/XenoBlue ~20"
   }

@endnode

@node "Configuration" "Configuration"
 You have to edit the @{"XenoBlue.setup" link "XBsetup" 0} file before you can start @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}.

You are allowed to change the following files as long as you do not change
the copyright message:

   ConfigurationHelp          (help screen for the configuration menu)
   ConfigurationMenu          (configuration menu)
   ConfigurationMenuExpert    (configuration menu for expert mode)
   Intro                      (introduction screen)
   MainMenu                   (main menu)
   MainMenuExpert             (main menu for expert mode)
   MainHelp                   (help screen for the main menu)

Note: If the cursor isn't at the right position load the menufile into a
hex editor and change the last character from 0A into 20.

   XenoBlue.TXT               (texts @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} displays on the screen)

There are 2 example files included for menuset 0 (ascii) and 1 (ansi).

Note: Do NOT delete the % codes as %c, %s and %d in XenoBlue.TXT. These are
variables used by @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}. You can change their position in the text but do
NOT delete them!

 Line 143:the uppercase characters used for the main menu.
 Line 144:the uppercase characters used for the configurations menu.

Do NOT use the same character twice in one line or ansi codes in these lines.
And make sure that you use the same characters in your menuscreen,
mainmenu(expert), configurationmenu(expert), mainhelp and configurationhelp.

 Line 145:the character used for YES, NO, ABORT (see line 7)


   @{"XenoBlue.bulletins" link "Bulletins" 0}         (bulletins that will be included in the packet)

@endnode

@node "Bulletins" "Bulletins"
 What's a bulletin? Well in this reader file you can put information for users
of @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}. For example if you have added or removed areas or other things
you want them to know.

Every time you add something to the XenoBlue.bulletins file @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} will add
it to the user's packet as a bulletin file. To prevent that a user gets the
file over and over again, you have to put a date above it. As long as a user
didn't download a packet on that date or later he/she will get that bulletin
with his/her packet.

Normally you will use the date you wrote it. That way the user will only get
the bulletin once. But you can also use a future date, that way users will get
that bulletin until the specified date. For example in January 1997 you could
write a bulletin with a "Happy new year" message dated 07-01-97.

The structure of the file is simple but it's important you use it correctly.
Every bulletin has it's own date header which consists of 5 '@' followed by
the desired date in dd-mm-yy format. Other characters are ignored.

So for example:

 @@@@@ 02-08-95 @@@@@@@@@@

Followed by the message text which can be any length. But be sure you keep the
length of all lines under 80 characters. If at all possible don't use ANSI
colors, some offline readers do not support this. You can use IBM character
graphics but that forces users to use an IBM.font.

A user will get a maximum of 5 bulletins, if there a more than 5 he/she will
only get the latest 5.

@endnode

@node "History" "History"
HIStory
------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Don't know what happened with earlier versions. :( I do know that there was a
MAXsBlue before @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}.

 Changes in 0.21
 --------------
 - Section flags better supported
 - Abort option after building a packet
 - INITIAL_MSGS option for maximum number of msgs at first download.

 Changes in 0.22
 ---------------
 - Error in flags recognition corrected
 - Error in checking uploaded files corrected

 Changes in 0.23
 ---------------
 - Error in reading default netmail route corrected

 Changes in 0.24
 ---------------
 - SEEN-BY lines are stripped correct now
 - Newfiles listings.  (no wordwrap yet)

 Changes in 0.25
 ---------------
 - Checking on 'From' field of uploaded messages
 - wordwrap on new file listings
 - Expert menu's
 - Password protection
 - Message written counter is stored

 Changes in 0.26
 ---------------
 - Message scanning should go a lot faster now...
 - Netmail shows name of addressed BBS.
 - Goodbye (after download)  XB doesn't log out itself yet, don't know how
:-(
 - More prompt at selecting on-line areas (not perfect...)
 - Crash problem hopefully fixed....

 Changes in 0.27
 ---------------
 - Few bugs corrected.  Oops!

 Changes in 0.28
 ---------------
 - Special fix for Xenolink 1.95.  There are now two versions:
 - @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text} for xlk 1.90 and XenoBlue195 for xlk 1.95 and higher.

 Changes in 0.29
 ---------------
 - Logoff function works, at last!

 Changes in 0.30
 ---------------
 - made on-line area selection more clear.
 - debug lines removed

 Changes in 0.31
 ---------------
 - BUGFIX:  Fidonet control info on/off should really work now... :-)
 - New setup keyword, "DEFAULT_SECT" indicates that a section must be
   connected for first-time users.
 - Shows logout.txt file from SystemText dir, at logging out via @{fg shine}Xeno@{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}.
 - on-line area selection slightly changed.

 Changes in 0.32
 ---------------
 - on-line area selection changed again. (we'll get there someday =)
 - maximum forced sections increased from 8 to 10.
 - sections with sysop access -> all messages downloaded
 - bulletin option
 - +ALL and -ALL at on-line area selection

 Changes in 0.33
 ---------------
 - bug removed in on-line area selection (izzienugoe?)
 - resetting last read pointers made possiblet. (first try)

 Changes in 0.34
 ---------------
 - With netmail messages to points only the BBS is looked up.
 - Namecontrol for personal messages made case-independant.
 - Setup file considerably changed!  Pay attention to this!!!
 - "Crash" and "Hold" netmail flags are supported.
 - Logs some things (suggestions?)

 Changes in 0.35-0.36
 --------------------
 - Crash netmail route address same as destination address
 - ALLOW_HANDLES flag no longer used
 - At offline area configuration only changes are reported.
 - Keyword UNLISTED_NODES to send netmail to unlisted nodes
 - Maximum packet size is now configurable with MAX_PACKET_SIZE

 Changes in 0.37-0.4
 -------------------
 - Sysop Access flag was not reset.

 Changes in 0.41-0.42c
 ---------------------
 - Leon Makkink hands source to Jos van Oijen
 - recompiled with SAS C 6.56 and new xenolink.h
 - Fileattach is possible (from BBS to caller)
 - ???

 Changes in 0.43-0.43b
 ---------------------
 - configurable texts (ansi)

 Changes in 0.44
 ---------------
 - NO hotkeys works

 Changes in 0.44b-0.45
 ---------------------
 - FORCE_SECTION & DEFAULT_SECTION maximum changed to 40
 - added more configurable texts

 Changes in 0.46
 ---------------
 - fixed XenoBlue.txt ansi version
 - configurable menutexts

 Changes in 0.46a
 ----------------
 - offline config bug fixed  (didn't store config with no download)

 Changes in 0.47
 ----------------
 - configurable Y/N and (not) hotkeyable Y/N questions

 Changes in 0.5
 --------------
 - fixed some small bugs
 - first public release

@endnode

